{
  "text": "Studies seldom consider antiherbivore defences when investigating the evolution of plant reproductive diversity. Recent research, however, highlights independent roles for both herbivory and antiherbivore defences in shaping natural selection on plant reproductive traits [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . In this study, we asked whether induced plant defences alter natural",
